clinical_study.brief_title: Bioequivalence of 5 Tablets of 100 Milligrams (mg) Versus 2 Tablets of 250 mg Tablet Formulation 3 (TF3) of Tepotinib
clinical_study.official_title: An Open-label, Single-dose, Randomized, 2-period, 2-sequence Cross-over, Single-center Phase I Trial in Healthy Subjects to Assess the Bioequivalence of Tepotinib Tablet Formulation 3 Administered as 5 Tablets of 100 mg Versus 2 Tablets of 250 mg Dose Strength.

lead_sponsor.agency: Merck Healthcare KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany, an affiliate of Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany

clinical_study.source: Merck Healthcare KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany, an affiliate of Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany

brief_summary.textblock: This study will investigate the bioequivalence of the 100 mg and 250 mg dose strengths of tepotinib TF3 when administered at the same dose under fasted condition.

primary_outcome.measure: Area Under the Plasma Concentration-Time Curve From Time Zero to the Last Quantifiable Concentration (AUC 0-t) of Tepotinib
primary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

primary_outcome.measure: Area Under the Plasma Concentration-Time Curve From Time Zero Extrapolated to Infinity (AUC 0-inf) of Tepotinib
primary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

primary_outcome.measure: Maximum Observed Plasma Concentration (Cmax) of Tepotinib
primary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

secondary_outcome.measure: Time to Reach the Maximum Plasma Concentration (tmax) of Tepotinib
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period
Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

secondary_outcome.measure: Apparent Total Body Clearance (CL/f) of Tepotinib
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

secondary_outcome.measure: Apparent Volume of Distribution (Vz/f) of Tepotinib
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Pre-dose up to 168 hours post-dose of each period

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Clinically Significant Changes in Laboratory Assessments, 12-lead Electrocardiogram (ECG) Findings and Vital Signs

arm_group.description: Participants will receive a single oral dose of test treatment of tepotinib TF3 (5 * 100 mg) in treatment period 1 followed by a single oral dose of reference treatment of tepotinib TF3 (2 * 250 mg) in treatment period 2. The treatment periods will be separated by 21 day washout period.

Participants will receive a single oral dose of reference treatment of tepotinib TF3 (2 * 250 mg) in treatment period 1 followed by a single oral dose of test treatment of tepotinib TF3 (5 * 100 mg) in treatment period 2. The treatment periods will be separated by 21 day washout period.

intervention.description: Participants will receive a single oral dose of test treatment of tepotinib TF3 (5 * 100 mg) in either treatment period 1 or 2.
Participants will receive a single oral dose of reference treatment of tepotinib TF3 (2 * 250 mg) in either treatment period 1 or 2.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Healthy participants of non-child bearing potential
- Body weight between 50 to 100 kilogram (kg)
- Body mass index (BMI) between 18.5 and 29.9 kilogram per meter square (kg/m^2)
- Other protocol defined inclusion criteria could apply
Exclusion Criteria:
- Participation in a clinical study within 60 days prior to first drug administration
- Whole blood donation or loss of greater than 450 milliliter (mL) within 60 days prior to first drug administration
- Any surgical or medical condition, or any other significant disease that could interfere with the study objectives, conduct, or evaluation
- Other protocol defined exclusion criteria could apply
